9. Refinery laws

These should govern the whole system.

Law 1

Not all data is equal.

Law 2

Outcome data outranks elegant theory.

Law 3

Narrative improves adoption but cannot certify truth.

Law 4

A useful refinery makes products, not just interpretations.

Law 5

Feedback loops matter more than input volume.

Law 6

If no product or update emerges, refinement failed.

